## ai-engkit DooD Network Awareness

ai-engkit uses **Docker-out-of-Docker (DooD)** mode: the `/var/run/docker.sock`
passthrough means `docker` commands inside this container operate the **host's**
Docker daemon. Sibling containers started via `docker compose up` live on a
separate bridge network — they are **not** reachable via `localhost` from here.

| Target location | `localhost` works? | Correct access |
|---|---|---|
| Process started **in this container** (directly) | ✅ Yes | `http://localhost:<port>` |
| OpenChamber Web UI (port 3000) | ✅ Yes | `http://localhost:3000` |
| **Sibling container** via `docker compose up` | ❌ No | `http://<bridge_gateway>:<mapped_port>` |
| **Host machine** service | ❌ No | `http://host.docker.internal:<port>` |

To reach a sibling container:
```bash
GATEWAY=$(docker network inspect <network-name> \
  --format '{{range .IPAM.Config}}{{.Gateway}}{{end}}')
# Then access via http://${GATEWAY}:<mapped_port>
```
